<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-732-921  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 732 921.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>EDGE: Work-Group Computing Report  Dec 24 1990 v1 n31 p4(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT EDGE Publishing 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>ATandamp;T - NCR; fallout: Sun Microsystems announces amended CommonShares Rights Agreement. (board of directors passes amendments toenable shareholders to exercise rights as soon as any party otherthan ATandamp;T acquires at least ten percent of NCR's common shares)andM;</TITLE><DESCRIPT>Company:   NCR Corp. (Management)American Telephone and Telegraph Co. (Acquisitions and mergers).andO;Ticker:    NCR; T.andO;Topic:     InvestmentsComputer IndustryPolicyGoals and ObjectivesCompaniesBoard of DirectorsStockholder Accounting.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>Sun Microsystems Inc. Tuesday announced that its board of directors hadamended its Common Shares Rights Agreement.andM;The amendments provide that shareholders may exercise their rights as soon asa person or a group, other than American Telephone and Telegraph Company,acquires 10 percent or more of the outstanding common shares.andM;American Telephone and Telegraph Company currently owns approximately 18.9percent of the outstanding shares of Sun common stock, and the amendments donot apply to ATandamp;T as long as ATandamp;T is in compliance with the terms of theCommon Stock Purchase Agreement between the two companies, which includes a20 percent standstill provision.andM;The company also announced that it would be filing a Form 8-K with theSecurities and Exchange Commission containing revised by-laws and the amendedCommon Shares Rights Agreement.andP;  The company said that its board believedthese changes were prudent in the current industry environment to fullyprotect shareholder value.andO;</TEXT></DOC>